## Jobs — `<%= @project.full_path %>`

Manage CI/CD jobs for this project. All requests require a personal access token passed in the `PRIVATE-TOKEN` header.

**Base URL:** <%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>

**Authentication:**

```bash
curl "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/jobs" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

---

### List Project Jobs

```bash
curl "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/jobs" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

**Query parameters:**

- `scope` (optional) — Filter by job status: `created`, `pending`, `running`, `success`, `failed`, `canceled`, `skipped`, `manual`, `scheduled`
- `page` (optional) — Page number (default: `1`)
- `per_page` (optional) — Items per page, max `100` (default: `20`)

**Response fields per job:**

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| `id` | Job ID |
| `name` | Job name from the CI configuration |
| `status` | Job status |
| `stage` | Stage name |
| `ref` | Branch or tag name |
| `sha` | Commit SHA |
| `allow_failure` | Whether the job is allowed to fail |
| `created_at` | Creation timestamp |
| `started_at` | Start timestamp |
| `finished_at` | Finish timestamp |
| `duration` | Duration in seconds |
| `queued_duration` | Time spent in queue before running |
| `web_url` | URL to view the job in the browser |
| `pipeline` | Nested object with `id`, `iid`, `ref`, `sha`, `status` |
| `user` | Nested object with `id`, `name`, `username` |

**Pagination headers returned:**

| Header | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `X-Total` | Total number of jobs |
| `X-Total-Pages` | Total number of pages |
| `X-Page` | Current page |
| `X-Per-Page` | Items per page |
| `X-Next-Page` | Next page number (empty if on last page) |
| `X-Prev-Page` | Previous page number (empty if on first page) |

---

### List Jobs for a Pipeline

```bash
curl "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/pipelines/:pipeline_id/jobs" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

- `:pipeline_id` — Pipeline ID
- Supports the same `scope` and pagination parameters as the project jobs list

---

### Get a Single Job

```bash
curl "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/jobs/:id" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

- `:id` — Job ID
- Returns `404 Not Found` if the job does not exist

---

### Get a Job Log (Trace)

```bash
curl "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/jobs/:id/trace" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

- `:id` — Job ID
- Returns `text/plain` content with the raw job log

---

### Retry a Job

```bash
curl -X POST "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/jobs/:id/retry" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

- `:id` — Job ID
- Returns `200 OK` with the new job object on success
- Returns `400 Bad Request` if the job is not retryable

---

### Cancel a Job

```bash
curl -X POST "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/jobs/:id/cancel" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

- `:id` — Job ID
- Returns `200 OK` with the job object on success
- Returns `400 Bad Request` if the job is not cancelable
